Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of numerical methods and error estimation techniques for biomechanical simulations, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, the use of Finite Element (FE) models and mesh generation from medical images suggests a connection to cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) and cs.MS (Mathematical Software). The focus on error estimation and optimization of the mesh suggests a connection to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The use of simulations for computer-assisted surgery suggests a connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
